    "details": "An uncontrolled resource consumption (memory leak) flaw was found in ZeroMQ's `src/xpub.cpp` in versions before 4.3.3. This flaw allows a remote unauthenticated attacker to send crafted PUB messages that consume excessive memory if the CURVE/ZAP authentication is disabled on the server, causing a denial of service. The highest threat from this vulnerability is to system availability.",
